cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.OS, cs.NI, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on distributed transaction processing and network performance, which are topics commonly studied in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses concurrency control protocols, which are relevant to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. The use of RDMA and network primitives is related to the Operating Systems (cs.OS) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of different protocols, which falls under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
